urls.title: What happened to those who spoke up about coronavirus in China?
urls.description: Two men in hazmat suits told businessman Fang Bin they had come to take him into quarantine. But the textile trader, in his 40s, wasn't ill and the men outside his Wuhan apartment weren't doctors.

text: China's disappeared: What happened to those who dared to speak up about coronavirus? https://t.co/dC8lQXsy9F
